    ```javascript
function minAddToMakeValid(s) {
    let result = 0, balance = 0;
    for (let c of s) {
        balance += (c === '(') ? 1 : -1;
        if (balance === -1) {
            result++;
            balance++;
        }
    }
    return result + balance;
}
```

    The algorithm iterates through the string `s`, maintaining a `balance` variable. If an opening parenthesis is encountered, the balance is incremented, and if a closing parenthesis is encountered, the balance is decremented. If the balance becomes -1, this means there is an unmatched closing parenthesis. In this case, we increment `result` (the minimum number of moves required to make the string valid) and adjust the balance. At the end, any remaining balance indicates unmatched opening parentheses, so we add this to `result`.

Complexity: O(n) where n is the length of the input string

